#note his last play strongly suggests that he has the Q and he's trying to set up QI at C9. He also might have wanted to turn over more tiles if he didn't already have the blank. The question is, is QI something I should be trying to block? After OD and then QI, I'm down 8 and can out-in-two to win as long as he didn't draw an out - unlikely, since he'll have 6 tiles. My tiles fit nicely at 15I, which seemed like it would allow me to go out first.  I also made a fishing play here allowing me to draw a GIO bingo, which isn't relevant if he blocks the lane with QI. However, It is good insurance in case he decides to try to score with an OK play. I can also play DEVELED because GINOT might draw more bingos here, but it also tends to make it tougher to win on spread in the endgame!
